  16.4.4 ESMF_IsFinalized - Query Finalized status of ESMF

   INTERFACE:
     function ESMF_IsFinalized(rc)

   RETURN VALUE:
       logical :: ESMF_IsFinalized

   ARGUMENTS:
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
       integer,                 intent(out), optional :: rc

   DESCRIPTION:

   Returns .true. if the framework has been finalized. This means that
   ESMF_Finalize() has been called. Otherwise returns .false.. If an error
   occurs, i.e. rc /= ESMF_SUCCESS is returned, the return value of the
   function will also be .false..

   The arguments are:

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

